{
  "texts": [
    "Existing QML models can accurately fit partially corrupted labels to quantum states.In addition to randomizing the labels, we also explore the effects of randomizing the input quantum states themselves and conclude: Observation 3.",
    "(Fitting random quantum states).",
    "Existing QML models can accurately fit labels to random quantum states.These randomization experiments result in a remarkably large generalization gap after training without changing the circuit structure, the number of parameters, the number of training examples, or the learning algorithm.",
    "As highlighted in ref.",
    "62 for classical learning models, these straightforward experiments have far-reaching implications:1."
  ]
}